verbs.description: outwell (third-person singular simple present outwells, present participle outwelling, simple past and past participle outwelled)

entries.meaning: (archaic, transitive, intransitive) To well outward; to issue forth.
examples: […]  Religion that rebuketh prophane lamentation, drinkes in the riuers of those dispaireful teares, which languorous ruth hath outwelled  […]
